A create endpoint isn't much without a read endpoint. Add the read RPC and return a declared service-local error when the order does not exist.

<LanguageTabs>
{#snippet ts()}

Add the schemas to `schemas.ts`:

```ts
export const GetOrderRequest = Type.Object({
  orderId: Type.String(),
});
export type GetOrderRequest = Static<typeof GetOrderRequest>;

export const GetOrderResponse = Type.Object({
  orderId: Type.String(),
  customerId: Type.String(),
  status: Type.String(),
  items: Type.Array(Type.Object({
    productId: Type.String(),
    quantity: Type.Number(),
  })),
});
export type GetOrderResponse = Static<typeof GetOrderResponse>;
```

When an order does not exist, return a declared service error instead of an ad-hoc `{ type, message }` object. Built-in Trellis errors cover platform failures such as validation, auth, transport, and unexpected internal errors. Domain failures belong to your service.

Create `errors.ts` next to `schemas.ts`:

```ts
import { defineError } from "@qlever-llc/trellis";
import { Type } from "@sinclair/typebox";

export const NotFoundError = defineError({
  type: "NotFoundError",
  fields: {
    resource: Type.String(),
    resourceId: Type.String(),
  },
  message: ({ resource, resourceId }) => `${resource} ${resourceId} not found`,
});

export const errors = {
  NotFoundError,
} as const;
```

Register `Orders.Get` in the contract's `rpc` section alongside `Orders.Create`. Also import and pass the error map to `defineServiceContract(...)`:

```ts
import { defineServiceContract } from "@qlever-llc/trellis";
import { errors } from "../errors.ts";
import * as schemas from "../schemas.ts";

export const ordersService = defineServiceContract(
  { schemas, errors },
  (ref) => ({
    // ...

    capabilities: {
      "orders.write": { /* ... */ },
      "orders.read": {
        displayName: "Read orders",
        description: "Read order records.",
      },
    },

    rpc: {
      "Orders.Create": { /* ... */ },
      "Orders.Get": {
        version: "v1",
        input: ref.schema("GetOrderRequest"),
        output: ref.schema("GetOrderResponse"),
        capabilities: { call: ["orders.read"] },
        errors: [ref.error("NotFoundError"), ref.error("UnexpectedError")],
      },
    },
  }),
);
```

Now add the typed read handler to `handlers/orders.ts`:

```ts
import { err, isErr, ok } from "@qlever-llc/trellis";
import { NotFoundError } from "../errors.ts";
import type {
  RpcHandlerArgs,
  RpcHandlerResult,
} from "../contracts/orders_service.ts";

type Args = RpcHandlerArgs<"Orders.Get">;
type Result = RpcHandlerResult<"Orders.Get">;

export async function getOrderHandler({
  input,
  trellis,
}: Args): Promise<Result> {
  const result = await trellis.kv.orders.get(input.orderId).take();
  if (isErr(result)) {
    return err(new NotFoundError({
      resource: "Order",
      resourceId: input.orderId,
    }));
  }

  return ok(result.value);
}
```

Mount it from `main.ts`:

```ts
import { getOrderHandler } from "./handlers/orders.ts";

await service.trellis.mount("Orders.Get", getOrderHandler);
```

`trellis.kv.orders.get(key)` returns a `Result<TypedKVEntry<Order>, KVError>`. When the key doesn't exist, it returns an `Err`. Translate that into a declared service-local `NotFoundError` for the caller.

Callers can now branch on the declared error class:

```ts
import { isErr } from "@qlever-llc/trellis";
import { NotFoundError } from "./errors.ts";

const result = await client.request("Orders.Get", { orderId: "ord_123" });
const value = result.take();

if (isErr(value) && value.error instanceof NotFoundError) {
  console.log(value.error.resource, value.error.resourceId);
}
```

Upgrade and restart as before.

{/snippet}
{#snippet rust()}

Add the schemas in `contracts/service.rs`:

```rust
fn get_order_request_schema() -> Value {
    json!({
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["orderId"],
        "properties": {
            "orderId": { "type": "string" }
        }
    })
}

fn get_order_response_schema() -> Value {
    order_schema()
}

fn not_found_error_schema() -> Value {
    json!({
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["id", "type", "message", "resource", "resourceId"],
        "properties": {
            "id": { "type": "string" },
            "type": { "type": "string", "const": "NotFoundError" },
            "message": { "type": "string" },
            "resource": { "type": "string" },
            "resourceId": { "type": "string" },
            "context": { "type": "object", "patternProperties": { "^.*$": {} } },
            "traceId": { "type": "string" }
        }
    })
}
```

Register the schemas, error, capability, and RPC:

```rust
.schema("GetOrderRequest", get_order_request_schema())
.schema("GetOrderResponse", get_order_response_schema())
.schema("NotFoundErrorData", not_found_error_schema())
.error("NotFoundError", "NotFoundError", "NotFoundErrorData")
.capability(
    "orders.read",
    ContractCapabilityMetadata {
        display_name: "Read orders".to_string(),
        description: "Read order records.".to_string(),
        consequence: None,
    },
)
.rpc(
    "Orders.Get",
    rpc("v1", "rpc.v1.Orders.Get", "GetOrderRequest", "GetOrderResponse")
        .with_call_capabilities(["orders.read"])
        .with_error_types(["NotFoundError", "UnexpectedError"]),
)
```

Add the handler:

```rust
use serde_json::json;
use trellis_sdk_orders_service::types::GetOrderRequest;
use trellis::service::{DeclaredRpcError, ServerError};

pub async fn get_order(
    context: Arc<AppContext>,
    _ctx: ServiceHandlerContext,
    input: GetOrderRequest,
) -> HandlerResult<Order> {
    let Some(bytes) = context.orders.get(&input.order_id).await? else {
        return Err(ServerError::DeclaredRpc(DeclaredRpcError::new(
            "NotFoundError",
            format!("Order {} not found", input.order_id),
            [
                ("resource", json!("Order")),
                ("resourceId", json!(input.order_id)),
            ],
        )));
    };

    Ok(serde_json::from_slice(&bytes)?)
}
```

Mount it with the generated registration helper:

```rust
service.register_orders_get({
    let context = Arc::clone(&context);
    move |ctx, input| handlers::get_order(Arc::clone(&context), ctx, input)
});
```

Callers see `NotFoundError` as a structured RPC error payload. Rust client code can branch on `RpcErrorPayload::error_type()` when a typed call returns `TrellisClientError::RpcError(...)`.

Upgrade and restart as before.

{/snippet}
